To facilitate the control of weapons when firing bursts, two pistol grips were installed - a rear one, instead of a rifle butt with a neck, and a front vertical one, in front of the magazine. the barrel is a round perforated casing, later replaced by ribs that improve barrel cooling. Due to milling, the cost of the weapon increased to $ 225 for a complete set, and the weight with an equipped 20-round magazine was up to 4,7 kg. However, this was offset by the power of the cartridge and rate of fire of almost 1000 rounds per minute, as well as the distribution of mass for the balance of the submachine gun [30]. minute[18].